.TH "tty_port_link_device" 9 "tty_port_link_device" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tty_port_link_device \- link tty and tty_port
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" tty_port_link_device
.BI "(struct tty_port *port "  ","
.BI "struct tty_driver *driver "  ","
.BI "unsigned index "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "port" 12
tty_port of the device
.IP "driver" 12
tty_driver for this device
.IP "index" 12
index of the tty
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Provide the tty layer with a link from a tty (specified by \fIindex\fP) to a
tty_port (\fIport\fP). Use this only if neither tty_port_register_device nor
tty_port_install is used in the driver. If used, this has to be called before
tty_register_driver.
